Rebecca: I enjoy the wide array of colors it has - very eye-catching. The stained glass reminds me of history, when people were able to figure out how to express themselves in art another way.
Preston: I chose it because of the extreme "eye-catching" effect that the glass has. It was mainly due to its size and bright colors for me.
Maheen: It is one of the simplest yet most beautiful pieces in the exhibit. When the light hits the glass at the perfect angle, you see all of these beautiful colors all over the floor and walls.
Ameena: I feel it is one of the [Museum’s] most recognizable pieces. When I visited the museum for the first time, I remember being in awe of it.

Cristina: Stained glass is always just so beautiful to look at. I don't even know if stained glass artwork can even be ugly. When light filters through stained glass it's stunning and enjoyable to look at.
